gmx:name.gco:CharacterString: Feature Catalog for Juvenile Salmonid Abundance Monitoring: Green Valley Creek, Russian River, California, 1991-2001

gmx:scope.gco:CharacterString: Coho salmon; Steelhead (Fish); Chinook salmon; Salmonid

gfc:definition.gco:CharacterString: Internal feature number.
Feature geometry.
Name of tributary

Location of index zone including stream name. Each stream was divided into upper, middle and lower reaches, based on elevation, average gradient, and distance from the Russian River and an index zone was select from surveys within each reach.
Three digit code for location of index zone. First letter represents stream reach (upper, middle, lower). Second and third letters represent two digit stream name. See attribute SEIN.
Unique numeric value for each sample record.
Location descriptor for index zone. See attribute SEIN.
Number of habitat units seined in each index zone.
Habitat unit identification number.
Habitat unit type (pool, riffle, glide). A unit is defined as a continuous portion of the stream of variable length, within which only one habitat type is present or is dominant.
Sampling date.
Sampling season. Summer is the beginning and fall is the end of the dry season.
Sampling year.
Total number of steelhead (Onchorhynchus mykiss) sampled within the index zone (all units combined).
Total number of coho (Onchorhynchus kisutch) sampled within the index zone (all units combined).
Total number of steelhead (Onchorhynchus mykiss) sampled within the habitat unit.
Total number of coho (Onchorhynchus kisutch) sampled within the habitat unit.
Survey results for presence/absence of suitable salmonid habitat. Yes = suitable habitat. NH = no habitat (unsuitable).
